Yesterday I did my first breath work session. 🌬️
These past few months have been some of the toughest times for me mentally and physically. I reached the point of absolute exhaustion. The lack of sleep, the steep learning curve of a new career, the doubt and lack of confidence has worn on me. I can feel it in my bones. Highly emotional, with the littlest thing sending me into tears, I was desperate to find something to help me. While this was the first of hopefully many more breath sessions, I already feel like I have moved something within me. I felt a release of energy that was stuck inside me. I am so grateful to have the experience and huge thank you to @lwzen for his guidance. 🙏🏻 
.

Meal prep with me for work this week 🍠🍌🥒🥑🍓

Brekkie: I like to keep it quick & easy with some overnight oats. Pro-tip: soak your oats, almond milk, chia seeds and cinnamon for 1/2 day, then add your favorite protein powder to make it nice and thick. I do 1:1 ratio of oats:almond milk. Top with berries/fruit & almond butter.

Snacks: @healthyeat_onthego bar or yogurt with 1/2 bar. Also love banana with nut butter. 

Lunch: @rachaelsgoodeats white bean tuna salad & crackers 

Dinner: Sausage tray-bake or leftover roasted salmon, veggies and sweet potato. Pop in oven to re-heat.

Dessert: @iheartmacros Sleep Collagen hot chocolate or a @sciencensoul cookie 🍪 (or both) 

Comment if you want to see more of my meal prepping 🤍

One of my daily breakfast staples these days: high protein Greek omelette with berries. Recipe & macro details below! 🍳🥑

- 30g diced peppers 
- 45g cherry tomatoes
- 5g olives 
- handful spinach 
- 184g egg whites
- one egg
- 28g fat free feta
- 40g avo
- 45g raspberries 

Macros: Carbs: 14.5g | Fat: 14g | Protein: 36g
